swipe👉
Pendulum Waves
.
Fifteen uncoupled simple pendulums of monotonically increasing lengths dance together to produce visual traveling waves, standing waves, beating, and (seemingly) random motion.
.
The period of one complete cycle of the dance is 60 seconds. The length of the longest pendulum has been adjusted so that it executes 51 oscillations in this 60 second period. The length of each successive shorter pendulum is carefully adjusted so that it executes one additional oscillation in this period. Thus, the 15th pendulum (shortest) undergoes 65 oscillations.
This apparatus was built from a design published by Richard Berg [Am J Phys 59(2), 186-187 (1991)] at the University of Maryland. The particular apparatus shown here was built by our own Nils Sorensen.
.

engineering? Then you've come to the

The Mercedes F1 engineknown as the M09 EQ Power+ is a new engine.
It hit the track in Barcelona, testing in February, and ran without any problems for 3,000 miles. It has thermal efficiency figures of around 50 percent and can produce 1,000 hp. Cowell and his engineers see even more potential for improvement and are excited about how their concepts could be applied to the road car. But why a new engine when the only big change is that drivers can only have three engines per season, rather than the previous limit of five? “The decision was driven by a number of new requirements,” Cowell says. “The biggest challenge was to obtain a 40 percent increase in the life of the hardware, in comparison with last year. We focused on trying to increase the life of the equipment without losing performance, but we also wanted to change the packaging of the power unit for the benefit of overall car performance. “The forces on the engine are higher because of increased cornering speeds and more grip, so we worked very closely with our colleagues in Brackley, trying to understand the best overall integration in the chassis, the transmission and the aerodynamic surfaces.” The secret, Cowell says, is in the integration. This is why the Mercedes factory car is faster than the cars with customer engines.
